blogs.name: Kim Kelly Stamp in The Narrative Arc
blogs.heading: If You Want to Be a Creator, Delete All (But Two) Social Media Platforms
blogs.description: In October 2022, during the whole Elon Musk debacle, I finally deleted Twitter from my phone. Around the same time, I also logged out of Instagram and Facebook. I had wanted to remove these distractions from my life for a while, and thanks to Elon’s shenanigans, I got the push to do so.

blogs.name: Jeremiah Warren
blogs.heading: 31 Photos From September 11th That You Have Never Seen
blogs.description: Contrast that to today where you have people shooting magazine covers on cell phones and uploading over 500,000 images to Instagram, Snapchat, Twitter, and Facebook every minute. We don’t hear about national tragedies on the news anymore, we read about them in our Twitter and Facebook feeds. Seconds after they happen.

blogs.name: Julie Zhuo in The Year of the Looking Glass
blogs.heading: How to Think About Your Career
blogs.description: If you had asked 22-year-old me what my “career aspirations” were, I would have looked at you blankly and then casually changed the subject to what programs you’d recommend to model cute 3D bunnies for a video game, or whether the writers of Alias would be so devious as to ship Sydney Bristow and Sark.

blogs.name: Mirijam Missbichler
blogs.heading: Why Japanese Websites Look So Different
blogs.description: Over the years, I have had many encounters with Japanese websites — be it researching visa requirements, planning trips, or simply ordering something online.
